Trainers Methodology I is a training program for TVET Trainers in using the competency-based training delivery approach for training and assessment.

A TVET Trainer is a professional who enables a trainee or a group of trainees to develop competencies to perform a particular trade or technical work.

TVET Trainer may assume various roles such as:
-Training Facilitator
-Competency Assessor
-Training Designer and Developer
-Training Supervisor

Trainer/Assessor Qualification for TM1
(Core Competency Requirements)
-Plan Training Sessions
-Facilitate Learning Sessions
-Supervise Work-Based Learning
-Conduct Competency Assessment
-Maintain Training Facilities
-Utilize electronic media in facilitating training


TRAINER vs ASSESSOR:
Trainer
-Trains trainees
-Conducts training in a training center / institution over a period of time
-Trainees undergo Institutional Assessment so he/she receives TRaining Certificate
-Can assess/evaluate his/her own trainees

Assessor
-Evaluates Candidates / Assesses from other institution
-Administers assessment in accredited assessment center in just 1 day
-Candidates undergo National Assessment so he/she receives National Certificate
-Cannot assess/evaluate his/ger own trainees



Levels of Competencies
Basic -  essential and skills applicable to all Qualificationm
Common - essential knowledge and skills applicable only to Sector. example. tourism sector includes the following qualification 
           like housekeeping, food & beverage, bartending, tour guiding, travel services, etc.
Core - Essential knowledge and skills applicable to a particular/specific qualification



CBT (Competency Based Training)
-it is a self-paced, individualized approach or training.
-It utilizes a set of principles and steps that ensures the mastery of learning and successful achievement of learning outcomes


Managing CBT vs TRadidional Programs

Traditional Approach
-Instructors focus on managing approach
-Most students enter at about the same time
-Student all cover the same material
-Students all proceed from one topic to the next at the same time
-The trainer controls the learning pace
-all students are usually tested once
-The trainer is involved in teaching

CBT Approach
-Trainers focus on managing learning
-Trainers enter vgarious times throughout the year
-Different trainers may be training for different occupations within the same program
-Each trainee moves on to the next task only after mastering the task they're currently woking
-Each trainee progresses at his or her own pace
-Each trainee is tested when ready to demonstrate mastery.
-The trainer must be able to answer


10 Basic Principles of Competency-based TVET
-The training shall be based on a curriculum developed from the competency standards (Training Regulations)
-Learning is modular in its structure
-Training delivery is learner-centered and should accommodate individualized and self-paced learning strategies
-Training is based on work that must be performed
-Training materials are directly related to the competency standards and the curriculum modules
-Assessment is based on the collection of evidence of the performance of the work to the industry required standard
-Training is based on both on-and-of-the-job components
-Training program allows for recognition of prior learning (RPL) or current competencies
-Training allows for multiple entry and exit
-Training programs are nationally accredited

























